 Port Elizabeth - Between 7  and 12 mm of rain was measured in Port Elizabeth overnight, the PE office of the South African Weather Service said on Wednesday. "23 mm was measured in East London and 25 mm in Grahamstown/Makandla," described Garth Sampson, South African Weather Service Client Liaison Officer (Eastern Cape Region). "Not much rain was recorded in the catchment area, with around 2 mm being recorded. "Conditions will gradually clear from the west."   Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One.   